\section{Molecular iodine}
The iodine molecule has been extensively studied \cite{Martin:1986a},\cite{Wei:1974a},\cite{Tellinghuisen:1978a},\cite{Gerstenkorn:1981a},\cite{Gerstenkorn:1991a},\cite{Lamrini:1993a},\cite{Lewis:1994a}; we seek to exploit this knowledge base in both our numerical studies and experimental efforts. In the visible region, the absorption spectrum of molecular iodine is dominated by transitions between the ground ``X'' electronic state and an upper excited electronic state called ``B'' \cite{Lewis:1993a}. Here we estimate the required beam parameters for coherent control and introduce the energy level structure.
